<p>

Created through the efforts of US <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../514/59514.xml">
Senator</link> <senator wordnetid="110578471" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../951/333951.xml">
J. William Fulbright</link></senator>
, for over 50 years the Fulbright Programme has been promoting peace and understanding through educational exchange. It is one of the most prestigious award programmes worldwide, operating in 144 countries and with 51 commissions. More Fulbright <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../412/18951412.xml">
alumni</link> have won <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../201/21201.xml">
Nobel Prizes</link> than those of any other academic programme, including two in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../502/35502.xml">
2002</link>.</p>

